Package: rjax
Type: Package
Title: R Interface to XLA via PJRT
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Troy", "Hernandez", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "troy@cornball.ai",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-4248-604X"))
Description: Direct access to XLA (Accelerated Linear Algebra) from R via the
    PJRT C API. Compiles and executes HLO programs on CPU, GPU, and TPU
    backends without requiring Python or JAX.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/cornball-ai/rjax
BugReports: https://github.com/cornball-ai/rjax/issues
SystemRequirements: XLA PJRT plugin (libpjrt_c_api_cpu.so or similar)
NeedsCompilation: yes
Suggests:
    tinytest
Encoding: UTF-8
